text: Mailiifterl is an Austrian nickname for the first computer working solely 0n transistors 0n the European mainland. It was built in 1955 at the Vienna University of Technology by Heinz Zemanek. The builder plays 0n a quote on an operating computer: 'If it is not the rapid calculation speed of American models that Whirlwind or Typhoon can achieve_ it will be enough for a Wiener Mailiifterl' The full name is Binar dezimaler Volltransistor- Rechenautomat.
